Subject: RE: Overdue Temporary Accommodation Refund - Action Required ASAP
Good Afternoon Raffaella,

Thank you for your patience,

I have completed my review of the outstanding payments on your contents cla=
im and arrange payment of the next $5,000 for temporary accommodation.  Ple=
ase confirm if this (and future temporary accommodation payments) can be ma=
de into the same account as the previous ones.  Once I receive confirmation=
 I will arrange payment urgently, with this usually being processed within =
3 =E2=80=93 5 business days.

I have also noted that you provided costs for vet fees.  These would not be=
 able to be reimbursed as the vet fees are not covered by the policy if you=
r pet is injured in an accident with a motor vehicle.

I can see Zach has already advised you that the water rates would not be ab=
le to be reimbursed.

I also am happy to confirm that future payments for temporary accommodation=
 will be acted upon far more promptly, I recommend sending these to costs t=
o the claims email address, and copying me into it as well.

Please let me know if you have any further questions.

Kind Regards
Lance
[cid:image001.png@01DC4F32.15ED61F0]
